canonical:
  title: 麻布夜雨
  author: 徐居正
  language: lzh
  text: 百年身世政悠悠夜雨江湖惹起愁袖裏歸田曾有賦已拚終老白鷗洲
  rtl: true
  vertical: true
lzh_formatted:
  title: 麻布夜雨
  author: 徐居正
  language: lzh
  text: 百年身世政悠悠。夜雨江湖惹起愁。袖裏歸田曾有賦。已拚終老白鷗洲。
korean:
  title: 마포 야우
  author: 서거정
  language: kor
  text: |-
    백년의 신세가 진정 유유하거니
    강호의 밤비 소리가 근심을 끌어 일으킨다
    소매 속에는 귀전한다는 부가 전부터 있어
    이미 흰 갈매기 물가에서 늙을 것 정했노라
  url: https://db.itkc.or.kr/dir/item?itemId=BT#dir/node?dataId=ITKC_BT_1365A_1450_020_0060&viewSync=OT
english:
  title: Night Rain at Mapo
  author: Seo Geo-jeong
  language: eng
  text: |-
    A hundred years of life drift on, endless and serene.
    Night rain on river and lake stirs up my melancholy.
    Within my sleeve, I carry an old poem of returning to fields—
    I have already resolved to grow old among the white gulls.
  footnotes:
    - Mapo (麻布) is a region near Seoul historically associated with solitude and contemplation
    - The 'white gulls' reference evokes the classical Chinese ideal of the recluse who dwells by water, removed from worldly affairs
    - The 'poem of returning to fields' alludes to the literati tradition of retreat from official life to rural seclusion
